Step 1) Make sure Java8u45 or greater is installed

Step 2) Install Clang:

Unix:
sudo apt-get install clang-3.6

Windows: See "installclang_windows" file for instructions perfected by my trial-and-error experiences.

Step 3) Target LLVM assembler. First, navigate to project folder. Inside should be a compiler.jar file. Run a test by calling these commands to compile one of the test programs (for information about the arguments, 

java -jar compiler.jar -s "final_programs\minimal.src" -o "out.ll" -show-ast
java -jar compiler.jar -s "final_programs\fibb.src" -o "out.ll" -show-ast
java -jar compiler.jar -s "final_programs\arrays_and_loops.src" -o "out.ll" -show-ast

For more information about the arguments, call help command:

java -jar compiler.jar --help

Step 4) Target system executable by using Clang to compile the generated LLVM assembler output file:

clang out.ll

Step 5) An executable file called "a" should now exist in the directory. Run the program:

./a